Even if cutting on the BDT output has been proven efficient to reduce not only ZZ but also the reducible background, 
this MVA method has not been used to produce the final results exposed in Sec.~\ref{sec:results}. 
The main reason is the lack of statistics in the signal region; the level of control of the backgrouns, especially the reducible one, 
has not been judged sufficient because of the small number of events. However, the estimated gain of such a method is superior to 20\%, and
 could be used in future runs with larger luminosity.

